Ad Text:
About The Architecture Practice 

At The Architecture Practice (TAP), we are focused on the needs of our clients and helping them achieve their strategic goals. Do you enjoy working with a motivated team? Being supported to do your best? and the ability to expand your experience? If so, please consider this your opportunity to see your work contribute to better outcomes for a broad number of clients.

We have established TAP as a thought leader to provide solutions that are practical today and scalable for tomorrow. We create collaborative teams dedicated to innovate and optimise each of our clients businesses.

With a strong culture of helping one another TAP will help you grow as an individual, offer you incredible career opportunities and support you to deliver amazing outcomes for every one of your clients.

In this role, you will be responsible for elicitation of requirements, documenting use cases, case studies, epics, process models and most important of all visualising business problems, goals, vision and objectives.

Current Demand Profile:

We currently have various vacancies for qualified and experienced Senior Business Analysts (both technical and non-technical) to join the TAP team in  Canberra, Sydney and Melbourne. Our values are built on a foundation of strong culture, ethics, and a determination to provide the same value to our clients. We believe the most important part is for them to align with the principles that we work from on a daily basis.

Primary responsibilities:

Visualisation of business needs, goals, objectives, problems and vision;

Elicitation and documentation of functional and non-functional requirements;

Documenting use cases, epics and/or case studies;

Supporting ICT Strategies, Business and Enterprise Architecture;

Working with Business and IT owners, architects, solution teams, development teams and infrastructure services to manage expectations;

Demonstrated business change and process re-engineering experience, including working with Business stakeholder to adopt to define and implement new ways of working;

Conducting vendor analysis for new capabilities as needed;

Participating in the design of system and application architectures on the basis of cost, functionality and practicality;

Preparing high-quality business and technical documentation;

Establishing effective relationships in order to facilitate fast decision making to meet deliverables and schedule;

Strong business acumen and customer-centric approach to delivery and a desire to work closely with clients to solve complex business problems in an efficient manner; and

Collaborating within and across teams to establish and document best practices in various functional/business areas.

Minimum 3-5+ Years experience in:

Agile delivery 

CRM 

Azure knowledge

Required Qualifications:

Undergraduate degree or equivalent experience of 5 or more years in Business Analysis;

Excellent written, interpersonal and oral communication skills; and

Experience in communicating complex technical information effectively and appropriately to Senior Executives and Business Stakeholders.

Mandatory Requirements:

Australian Citizens Only;

AGSVA Security Cleared; and 

Located in Canberra, Sydney or Melbourne.

Why Join Us?

TAP works as one big family that supports, develops, and nurtures talent. With a wide variety of clients and opportunities we believe that we offer a work environment for individuals to flourish and learn.

Interesting and varied work projects

Support for continuing your professional development through inhouse training and external conferences

Flat management structure

Yearly performance/pay reviews

Strong social culture and down-to-earth environment

Flexible working environment
